-- Australia shares set to open higher tracking Wall Street
-- By Cecile Lefort
-- Sun Dec 28, 2014 05:39PM EST
-- None



SYDNEY, Dec 29 (Reuters) - Australian shares are likely to have a firm start on Monday after Wall Street closed at records on Friday.

The S&P/ASX 200 index <.AXJO> edged up in a shortened Christmas Eve session, while New Zealand's benchmark NZX 50 index <.NZ50> eased 0.2 percent in early trade, a whisker away from record highs touched last week. For a summary of overnight action across global markets, double click on [AU/CALL]